'''Schneider's pitta''' ('''''Hydrornis schneideri''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Pittidae]]. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Sumatra]] in [[Indonesia]].  Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]]. It was rediscovered in 1988 after last being seen in 1918.

